<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 13 (MENA)--Iran has started setting up 
a nuclear power plant in Bushehr Province south of Tehran with 
the aid of Russian experts. 
  An informed Iranian source told reporters today that an 
agreement was reached with the Russian authorities a few months 
ago on the implementation of the first phase of the facility. 
  Construction of the project, which will take four years to 
operate with full capacity, started in March, the source said. 
As much as 30,000 tonnes of necessary materials were 
transported from Germany to Iran, he said. The German 
Government refused however to ferry another 7,000 tonnes, he 
added. [words indistinct] 

