<F P=102>   LD2104124994 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1100 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The commander of the Strategic Forces Division, 
General (Mosad Sagoyev), says that Russia is loyal to its 
international obligations under the SALT II treaty [as heard]. 
A group of journalists was allowed to visit the division, that 
is deployed in the Volga region. They visited the headquarters 
and got acquainted with combat equipment of the division. 
  General (Sagoyev) reported that the SS-20 medium range 
missiles had been liquidated in keeping with the treaty. As for 
the strategic missiles, they are targeted nowhere. They will be 
assigned a special task, the commander said, only in case of an 
attack on Russia. 

