<H3> <TI>   Hamas Reportedly Pledges Not To Attack Qatif Settlements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Reportedly Pledges Not To Attack Qatif Settlements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604105594 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 26 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA2604105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Pinhas 'Inbari] </F>
  [Text] The agreement between Fatah and Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] in Gaza contains a secret clause in which 
Hamas pledges not to attack the Qatif Bloc settlements, our 
correspondent has learned from Fatah sources in the territories. 
According to the sources, this reflects the most recent Hamas 
line -- namely, that the organization will not obstruct 
Palestinian rule in Gaza and Jericho. The sources claim that 
this clause has created tension between the Islamic Jihad and 
Hamas, as well as between two Hamas branches: the pro-peace 
Ahmad Yasin branch and the branch comprising the 10 rejectionist 
organizations that oppose the agreement. 
  [A related report by Dan Avidan on page 2 of Tel Aviv DAVAR 
in Hebrew on 26 April cites "Arab sources" as saying that "PLO 
and Hamas delegations are conducting secret negotiations in 
Cairo in an attempt to conceptualize the ties between the two 
movements on the eve of the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho" and that "the PLO-Hamas 
encounter was arranged through the mediation of Hamad 
Abu-al-Nasr and Sayf al-Din al-Banna, leaders of the Muslim 
Brotherhood movement in Egypt."] 

</TEXT>

