  [Text] The Central Bureau of Investigation [CBI] has found 
evidence that arms training was imparted in a neighboring 
country to some of the accused in last year's Bombay blasts. A 
CBI spokesman said that two people have been arrested in this 
connection. The Bureau is said to have gathered more material 
against the prime accused in this case. It is alleged that the 
two arrested were sent abroad for training in handling 
explosives by another accused who is absconding. The CBI is 
reported to have made the breakthrough while checking the 
records of the regional passport office. 

