<H3> <TI>   Deputy Says France Places Country on Terrorism List </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Says France Places Country on Terrorism List </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2604134994 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 25-26 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2604134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] AKHIR KHABAR has learned that the French interior 
minister has placed Jordan on the list of states sponsoring 
terrorism in the world, imposed restrictions on the movement of 
Jordanian nationals in France, and forced them to obtain exit 
permits before leaving France. In a statement to AKHIR KHABAR, 
Deputy Muhammad Abu-'Alim, who recently returned from an 
official visit to the French capital, said that he, as well as 
the Arab delegations participating in the Arab-European 
parliamentary dialogue, were surprised at the official French 
stand vis-a-vis Jordan. He added that they discussed the matter 
with the French officials, particularly since we in Jordan are 
not aware of this matter. 
  Abu-'Alim said: The Jordanian Embassy in Paris is aware of 
this. I personally met with Mr. Bouchar [name as published] who 
is currently the head of the Middle East Political Desk at the 
French Foreign Ministry. He added that the French official 
admitted that Jordan was mistakenly placed on the terrorism 
list. The French official said: The French Government will 
discuss the matter. 
  AKHIR KHABAR has also learned that the [Jordanian] 
Government 
is currently holding contacts with the French officials in this 
regard and that it expects the situation to be addressed before 
declaring the official French stand which is known to French 
political figures. 
  The French foreign minister visited Israel three weeks ago 
and refused the meet the Jordanian deputies who visited Paris. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

