<H3> <TI>   `Sought After' ETA Terrorist Arrested in Barcelona </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Sought After' ETA Terrorist Arrested in Barcelona </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804201394 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid TVE Internacional Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Felipe San Epifanio, one of the most sought 
after Basque Fatherland and Liberty [ETA] terrorists in recent 
months, was arrested at 1500 in a bar in the Olympic marina in 
Barcelona. The terrorist was armed and resisted arrest. [passage 
omitted] 
  After the arrest of Felipe San Epifanio, aka Pipe, three 
other suspected terrorists linked with the attacks perpetrated 
in Barcelona in recent months are being sought by the police. 
They are Gregorio Vicario Setien, Rosario Ezkerra Perez de 
Nanclares, and Dulos Lopez Resines. 

</TEXT>

