<H3> <TI>   `Large Explosion' Rocks Johannesburg's Jan Smuts Airport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Large Explosion' Rocks Johannesburg's Jan Smuts Airport </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Police Questioning Suspect </H4>

<F P=102> MB2704074994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0736 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2704074994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg April 27 SAPA -- Police were 
questioning a suspect who matched the description of a white man 
seen running away from a car shortly before Jan Smuts airport 
was rocked by a powerful car bomb on Wednesday. SAP [South 
African Police] spokesman Capt Wikus Webber said the suspect had 
been driving a white Toyota. He was fairly tall and had long 
brown hair. 
  Police confirmed there had been no deaths as a result of the 
blast but said two injured people were in a serious condition. 
Police confirmed the blast had been a car bomb. 
  Airport workers were still cleaning up debris -- mostly 
shattered glass -- at 9.30AM after the 7.15AM blast. At least 
18 people were injured in the blast. 

</TEXT>

