CSO 

    Editor's Note: The FBIS Terrorism Desk welcomes 
suscribers' comments and suggestions at (703) 733-5512. 
  Highlights and major incidents in this edition of 
the FBIS Terrorism Report include: 
<H5>  Algeria/Italy </H5>
  Italian police raided what appears to be an Islamic 
Salvation Front (FIS) safehouse in Perugia, confiscating 
weapons-training videos and false passports. 
<H5>  Egypt/U.S. </H5>
  Cairo newspaper AL-AHRAM AL-MASA'I says that Egypt will 
ask U.S. authorities through Interpol to deport Shaykh 'Umar 
'Abd-al-Rahman after his 28 April sentencing in an Egyptian 
court. 
<H5>  Palestinians/Germany </H5>
  DER SPIEGEL reports that PFLP-GC member Marwan Khreesat, 
arrested in Germany in the 1988 "Autumn Leaves" operation, was 
an "agent" for the German Federal Office of Criminal 
Investigation (BKA). 
<H5>  Palestinians/Lebanon </H5>
  "Palestinian sources" told Cairo's MENA news agency that 
Fatah will withdraw its "military and semi-military presence" 
from Lebanon. 
<H5>  Turkey/Germany </H5>
  A German TV program has run footage of explosives training 
conducted in a northern Iraq PKK camp. See "Selected Video 
Reports" below. 
  A former PKK official who was planning to leave the party 
was shot in Germany. 

</TEXT>

