<H3> <TI>   Grenade Thrown at Restaurant; Six Foreigners Hurt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grenade Thrown at Restaurant; Six Foreigners Hurt </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    European Restaurant </H4>

<F P=102> AB0405095194 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 0730 GMT 4 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0405095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville Africa No. 1 </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Violence is back on the agenda in Lome, Togo. 
Five Frenchmen and a Beninese were injured in the Togolese 
capital last night when a grenade thrown into a restaurant in 
the Be district exploded. The six victims are not in danger of 
death and the Togolese police have declined at this stage of 
their inquiry to speculate on the reasons behind the attack. 
The targeted restaurant belongs to a Frenchman and is known to 
be mostly patronized by Europeans. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

