<H3> <TI>   Unidentified Body, 100 Kg of TNT Powder Discovered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unidentified Body, 100 Kg of TNT Powder Discovered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305161494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1440 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 May (MENA)--Security forces in Asyut have 
found the body of a 25-year-old bearded man, wearing peasant's 
clothes on the eastern desert leading to Asyut. The body was 
riddled with bullets. 
  This was according to an Interior Ministry security source, 
who added that the security forces found the body lying near an 
automatic rifle bearing serial number 6245 and 12 bullets, one 
inside the rifle barrel, and 11 empty cartridge cases. They 
also discovered one plastic bag three meters away from the body 
and another ten meters away each containing 50 kg of TNT. 
  An unidentified person telephoned the Abnub police station 
and said that while he was driving on the desert road to Suhaj 
at 0300 today he saw people exchanging gunfire which forced him 
to quickly return to report the incident. He said the site was 
around two km south of the eastern approach to Asyut. 
  The security forces, the criminal laboratory experts, and 
the 
police moved to the area where they found scattered cases used 
for packing fruits, men's clothes dropped on the sand beside the 
road, and a small rug. 
  The public prosecution office has been informed and 
investigations are underway to identify the body. 
  The interior ministry will issue a statement later on the 
incident. 

</TEXT>

